【Large Storage Capacity】 The actual usable capacity of the USB flash drive is about 92% of the specified capacity, because part of the space is used for the normal function of the USB flash drive, and there are different algorithms for computers and USB flash drives. Computer 1GB = 1024MB, USB flash drive 1GB = 1000MB.

【Transfer Performance】 The USB flash drive can achieve fast and stable data transfer, with read speeds of up to 60-90 MB/s and write speeds of up to 20-40 MB/s. (Test Environment USB 3.0 PC, Test Software H2testw) Note: Compatible with USB 2.0 interface, but with limited speed.

【Wide Compatibility】 USB flash drives compliant with USB 3.0 standard and the following standards for PC/laptop/TV, etc. Default format is exFAT, if you need FAT32 format USB flash drive, you need to format it to FAT32 format and then use it.

【Quality Guarantee】Our thumb drive has Strict control of product quality and is tested rigorously before shipping. If there are any problems with the USB drive, please contact us the first time, and questions will be responded to within 24 hours. With a 12-Months Warranty, we will provide you with either a refund or a replacement.
body.description: USB Stick for PC and Laptop SANKESU USB stick can work with PC and laptop easily, please make sure the device port is in good condition before use. If there is a physical failure in the USB port of other devices, the flash disk will not work properly. You can choose other USB ports. USB Stick for Car Audio/TV/Speaker/Printer... If the USB stick can not work with the car audio/TV/speaker/printer, we advise that you can format the USB stick to FAT32 by software(Like: DiskGenius). Some devices can only recognize the FAT32. We don't advise the large capacity usb stick for them, the devices' expandable memory is less than 128GB.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars These incredibly flimsy drives were not even worth the packaging that they came in. Here's
reviews.reviewText: okay so here's the thing, I bought these drives for just under $10 thinking they would be inexpensive for just simple use. No I didn't expect them to be rugged at all but the flimsy material that they were made out of made the electronics inside rattle while inserting the drive in any USB port the plastic clicked back and forth and the drive never Stay powered on for any length of time making it impossible to use. It was a two pack so I tried the other one and it worked fine except for after I removed it and then later put it back in a different USB port and then it failed as well the funny part about this is that Amazon will not give a refund for this item unless I send it back, and I see that as a waste of my $10 and the 799 they wanted to charge me for the return mailer. I'm disabled and I don't have a lot of money but when this drive fell apart see the second picture then it suddenly started working, it's my guess that the casing for the drive was causing the electronics to short out or something. So if I could give this zero stars yes I would. And I'm not going to return it unfortunately but I'm not going to go cheap on USB drives ever again.

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Over all I would say this is a pretty good buy for the price. It appears to be working well. Plug an Play. Nothing fancy to figure out. I dropped an audiobook in there to test it and it was faster than other USB that I have. My only draw back was I thought I was getting 500GB - Brand new it says that 1.12 MB was used which is understandable (its a fairly small amount) but where did a 32Gig chunk go? As you can see from the pictures I took it shows details brand new. I'm not a computer wiz but I think I got ripped off as its not as promised.Physically as you can see from the video, The USB is a bit loose from the cover its attached to. Its swing around. Hopefully It doesn't come lose or God forbid I lose it.All in all its a pretty good buy for the price. I'm happy with my purchase - Don't expect to get 500GB or you will be disappointed.I read somewhere on the internet that if you have PC - it calculates storage using an older calculation as suppose to Mac and other OS which uses the newer way to calculate the storage space. So that could be it. I don't know much about this stuff. I'm grateful for the 468GB that it shows.I still would recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Compatible with Windows , Mac and Linux
reviews.reviewText: * PhysicalThis pen drive is available in several sizes of capacity. This device is USB3.0 A port+ Type C 3.1 port compatible with both USB 3.0 and USB 2.0 ports. When I bought it I took the cover off and immediately thought it was not USB 2.0 compatible as it would not fit into the USB 2.0 socket! But it has two interfaces, both C3.1 AND USB 3.0. It's just two interfaces at opposite ends of the thumb drive. USB 3.0 is backwards compatible with USB 2.0. The speed just runs at USB 2.0 speeds in USB 2.0 ports. The greater capacity means a slower connection than USB 2.0. In theory, it is supposed to be 10x faster with USB 3.0, but in real-world conditions, it's around 4 or five times more rapid data transfer rates. I have USB 3.0 so it's great. The price is great too. In the first years of thumb drives, 64Meg cost £26. This pen drive is 1000x capacity at a quarter the cost. Moores law strikes again!
